ie.gmit.sw

Class QueryProcess

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.gmit.sw.QueryProcess

  • public class QueryProcess
extends java.lang.Object
    This class uses ExecutorService where ThreadPool is created. Multiple threads runs the FileParser to read the file. And another ThreadPool submit QueryShingleTaker. Where the results of that ThreadPool are assigned to Future interface to generate the ConcurrentHashMap.
    Since:
    1.8
    See Also:
    ExecutorService

      • queryFileRead

        public java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> queryFileRead(java.lang.String fileName,
                                                                                                int queueSize,
                                                                                                int poolSize)
                                                                                         throws java.lang.InterruptedException,
                                                                                                java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException
        This method runs multiple threads to get BlockingQueue populated in the FileParser class and generates the ConcurrentHashMap with the help of Future interface.
        Parameters:
        fileName - Name of the file
        queueSize - Size of the BlockingQueue. (Maximum capacity)
        poolSize - Size of the ThreadPool
        Returns:
        ConcurrentHashMap where String is the Shingle and the Integer is the number of appearance of that Shingle in the file.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - - Exception if Interrupted
        java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException - Exception during execution
